 work and relationship with municipalities, she has expertise in growth management, SEPA compliance, shorelines, transportation, critical areas, TDRs (Transfers of Development Rights) and environmental mitigation.  Ms. Orrico’s experience has also been enhanced by her work as a land use hearing examiner, and her role as the Chair of the Bellevue Planning Commission, overseeing creation and adoption of the Bel-Red Corridor Plan, which provides for the transformation of a 900-acre urban site into the largest mixed use, transit-oriented development in the country</p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" locked=\"off\"][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\" _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_text_color=\"#1d2639\" text_font_size=\"18px\" header_text_color=\"#1d2639\" header_font_size=\"32px\" header_3_font=\"|700|||||||\" header_3_text_color=\"#1d2639\" header_3_font_size=\"24px\" hover_enabled=\"0\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"]<h3>Business Practice</h3>\n<p><span>In addition to her real estate transactional work, Ms. Orrico is well-versed in general business matters and transactions.  She has represented large corporations, medium and small businesses, family- and women-owned businesses, and individuals. She has assisted clients with all aspects of their businesses, including complex transactional matters, and corporate matters including drafting and negotiating a wide range of contracts; corporate formation, maintenance, and licensing; shareholders’ agreements; dispute resolution and enforcement, and commercial litigation.</span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" locked=\"off\"][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\" _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_text_color=\"#1d2639\" text_font_size=\"18px\" header_text_color=\"#1d2639\" header_font_size=\"32px\" header_3_font=\"|700|||||||\" header_3_text_color=\"#1d2639\" header_3_font_size=\"24px\" custom_padding=\"0px|||||\" hover_enabled=\"0\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"]<h3>Community Service</h3>\n<p><span>Ms. Orrico is very active in the community.   She currently serves on the Board of Trustees for UW Medicine-Valley Medical Center.  She previously served as a Trustee and Past Chair of the Bellevue College Board of Trustees, and as a board member of the Washington State Trustees Association of Community and Technical Colleges.  She also served as a Board Member for Youth Eastside Services and the Issaquah Economic Vitality Commission.  Previously, she served as Chair of the City of Bellevue Planning Commission and Co-Chaired the Center for Women and Democracy Board with Duana Kolouskova.  She is a past member of the Overlake Hospital Foundation Board of Trustees, holding several leadership positions. Ms. Orrico also served as Vice-Chair as well as Chair of the Small Business Subcommittee for the Pacific Northwest Citizen Advocacy Panel for Improving IRS Service, a position to which she was appointed by the U.S. Secretary of Treasury.</span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_column _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" type=\"4_4\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" text_text_color=\"#1d2639\" text_font_size=\"18px\" header_text_color=\"#1d2639\" header_font_size=\"32px\" header_3_font=\"|700|||||||\" header_3_text_color=\"#1d2639\" header_3_font_size=\"24px\" hover_enabled=\"0\" locked=\"off\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"]<h3>Education</h3>\n<p><span>Ms. Orrico earned her juris doctorate in 1986 and bachelor’s degree in 1983 from the University of Wisconsin.    She served as a law clerk to the Honorable James Boll (1985-86) and legal intern to the Wisconsin Court of Appeals (1984-85).</span></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" locked=\"off\"][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\" _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" link_font=\"||||on|||#1d2639|\" link_text_color=\"#1d2639\" link_font_size=\"24px\"]<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.jmmklanduselaw.com/our-people\">Back to All Profiles</a></p>[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" custom_css_main_element=\"font-family: franklin-gothic-urw, sans-serif;\" locked=\"off\"][et_pb_row _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\" _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\"][et_pb_text _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" header_font=\"|700|||||||\" header_text_color=\"#272f3f\" header_font_size=\"40px\"]<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">Interested in partnering with us?</h1>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_button button_url=\"http://www.jmmklanduselaw.com/contact\" button_text=\"CONTACT US\" button_alignment=\"center\" _builder_version=\"4.9.5\" _module_preset=\"default\" custom_button=\"on\" button_text_color=\"#FFFFFF\" button_bg_color=\"#272f3f\" hover_enabled=\"0\" locked=\"off\" sticky_enabled=\"0\"][/et_pb_button][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]','Vicki Orrico','','inherit','closed','closed','','185-revision-v1','','','2021-06-11 00:29:51','2021-06-11 00:29:51','',185,'http://jmmk-law.local/?p=190',0,'revision','',0);
